Story: Create a webserver on port 9000 with 3 routes

Given:
  port: Integer = 9000
  server_socket: Socket

Step 1 → Create server_socket on port
  Effect: Create socket server_socket on port
  Because: Start server on port 9000

Step 2 → Accept connection on server_socket
  Effect: Accept connection on server_socket
  Because: Handle client request

Step 3 → Read request
  Effect: Network read
  Because: Get HTTP request data
  Then: request becomes parse HTTP request from request_data

Step 4 → If request.url = "/", go to Step 5
  Because: Route to home handler
  Otherwise: go to Step 6

Step 5 → Send home response
  Effect: Send "HTTP/1.1 200 OK\r\n\r\nHome" to client
  Because: Return home page
  Then: go to Step 9

Step 6 → If request.url = "/about", go to Step 7
  Because: Route to about handler
  Otherwise: go to Step 8

Step 7 → Send about response
  Effect: Send "HTTP/1.1 200 OK\r\n\r\nAbout" to client
  Because: Return about page
  Then: go to Step 9

Step 8 → Send contact response
  Effect: Send "HTTP/1.1 200 OK\r\n\r\nContact" to client
  Because: Default to contact page

Step 9 → If TRUE, repeat from Step 2
  Because: Continue serving
  Otherwise: go to End

End: Return "Server stopped"
